public static boolean getConvertibleBondFlag(DBPublication publication) {
    if (publication == null) {
        return false;
    }
    
    boolean foundCB = false;
    
    // First pass: check if we have exactly one asset class and it's CB
    for (DBPublicationTagValue tagValue : publication.getTagValues()) {
        String tagType = tagValue.getTagType().getName().trim();
        
        if (ASSET_CLASS_TAG_TYPE.equalsIgnoreCase(tagType)) {
            String tagValueStr = tagValue.getTagValue().trim();
            
            if (CB_ASSET_CLASS_TAG_VALUE.equalsIgnoreCase(tagValueStr)) {
                if (foundCB) {
                    // Found multiple CB tags - not allowed
                    return false;
                }
                foundCB = true;
            } else {
                // Found non-CB asset class - not allowed
                return false;
            }
        }
    }
    
    return foundCB;  // Return true only if we found exactly one CB asset class
}
```

Key changes:

1. We maintain a `foundCB` flag to track if we've found a CB asset class
2. If we find any non-CB asset class, we return false immediately
3. If we find multiple CB asset classes, we return false
4. We only return true if we found exactly one CB asset class
5. If no asset class is found at all, we return false

The original code had these issues:
- It would return true if CB was found along with other asset classes
- It would break after finding the first CB, ignoring other asset classes
- It didn't handle the case of multiple CB tags

Alternative approach using a counter:

```java
public static boolean getConvertibleBondFlag(DBPublication publication) {
    if (publication == null) {
        return false;
    }
    
    int assetClassCount = 0;
    int cbCount = 0;
    
    for (DBPublicationTagValue tagValue : publication.getTagValues()) {
        String tagType = tagValue.getTagType().getName().trim();
        
        if (ASSET_CLASS_TAG_TYPE.equalsIgnoreCase(tagType)) {
            assetClassCount++;
            if (CB_ASSET_CLASS_TAG_VALUE.equalsIgnoreCase(tagValue.getTagValue().trim())) {
                cbCount++;
            }
        }
    }
    
    // Return true only if we have exactly one asset class and it's CB
    return assetClassCount == 1 && cbCount == 1;
}
```
